Use the standard library
This is how to odd_count of lst:
  Remember that result is []
  Do this lst's length times:
    Remember that current is item 0 in lst
    Remember that count is 0
    Do this current's length times:
      Remember that ch is item 0 in current
      When remainder of toint of ch and 2 is 1, then:
        Increase count by 1
      End when
      Remember that current is item 1 in current
    End do
    Add result to "the number of odd elements {count}n the str{count}ng {count} of the {count}nput."
    Remember that lst is item 1 in lst
  End do
  The answer is result
